commit.message: Updating to 1.2.1
Added a automatic check via grep for debug print statements, so issue #43 does not happen again.
Fixes #43, I left a debug print statement.
Now uploads documentation automatically.
Updated versions for 1.2
Added targets for 3.1 and 3.3
Docs now reflect changes for 1.2
Switching to the readthedocs theme. Handles all my code examples better.
Improved auto detection for kanji, when not using shift-jis
Improved how input encodings is handled for kanji
Removing Jython tox test support. I cannot get it to run. Always says that python 2.5 is not supported.
Only generates coverage report for python 3.4, speeds testing enourmously.
xbm now passes tests on all supported platforms
Adding docs and tests for xbm support.
Adding entries for update to 1.2
Merge branch 'svanheulen-master'
Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/svanheulen/pyqrcode into svanheulen-master
Merge branch 'luzfcb-base64_png'
Renamed a test to have test_ prefix so it matches others.
Basic test code cleanup.
Cleaned up documentation.
Fixed wierd permissions on builder.py
Changed png_as_base64_str docs to refer to png. Should make maintenance easier.
Moved two imports to the method they acutally used with.
Merge branch 'base64_png' of https://github.com/luzfcb/pyqrcode into luzfcb-base64_png
Cleaned up the publication script.
Added X BitMap format.
add option to generate qrcode as base64 encoded PNG string
Adding pip freeze requirements list.
Updating to version 1.1.1 for distribution.
